Former MFM assistant coach and Arsenal youth coach scout Marcellinus Anyanwu has admonished the Nigeria Football Federation to be more aggressive and technical in youth programs for their wards to be among world best football nations. The assistant to former Nigeria international Nduka Ugbade said more deliberate and articulate support by the NFF through engaging technical sound and experienced coaches like him would be a big boost to Nigerian football. Anyanwu who coached Arsenal, Feyenoord academies and Universal Sports Academy in Dubai stated that top teams are investing on youth development as it provides the right platform for higher level. Anyanwu said: “Nigeria simply need experts to be fully supported by the NFF . We have more talents begging to be discovered. I’m ready to contribute my quota towards development of Nigerian football even as I’m close to joining the Benfica Football Academy in Dubai any moment from now “.